etymologies: late 18th century. From Dutch oliekoek, †olycoeck (Middle Dutch olikoeck) from olie + koek

definitions: A small ball-shaped cake made of sweetened dough and traditionally fried in lard (similar to a doughnut).

notes.text: Olykoeks originated in Dutch cookery and were introduced to America by early 17th-cent. Dutch settlers in New York.
